1
00:03:34,523 --> 00:03:37,976
[HOWLING]

2
00:03:47,164 --> 00:03:48,781
[GASPS]

3
00:03:49,695 --> 00:03:52,797
[WIND BLOWING]

4
00:03:53,516 --> 00:03:54,125
[GASPS]

5
00:04:01,559 --> 00:04:02,700
[GASPS]

6
00:04:21,922 --> 00:04:24,711
[LAUGHING]

7
00:04:27,906 --> 00:04:29,056
Money!

8
00:04:30,039 --> 00:04:32,839
Money! Money is coming in!

9
00:04:32,891 --> 00:04:35,235
Money is coming from the top,
from the bottom!

10
00:04:35,260 --> 00:04:36,827
Only money!

11
00:04:37,570 --> 00:04:39,029
The money is colour, the money is beauty!

12
00:04:39,070 --> 00:04:40,683
A man is nothing without money.

13
00:04:40,735 --> 00:04:46,099
Money, all over the place.
Money is raining.

14
00:04:47,939 --> 00:04:51,186
Soft money! What a money!

15
00:04:51,223 --> 00:04:53,070
Silky money! My money! So much money.

16
00:04:53,095 --> 00:04:55,499
- He is dreaming again.
- Money!

17
00:04:55,524 --> 00:04:57,855
Why are you tearing the mattress?
Come to your senses.

18
00:04:57,890 --> 00:05:00,088
- Sir!
- What are you doing? Bring some water.

19
00:05:00,242 --> 00:05:03,173
- Money is raining?
- What are you doing?

20
00:05:04,128 --> 00:05:05,730
- Money!
- Come to your senses.

21
00:05:05,751 --> 00:05:08,772
- Money!
- Come to your senses.

22
00:05:09,352 --> 00:05:11,900
The flood.

23
00:05:12,023 --> 00:05:13,264
Come to your senses.

24
00:05:18,448 --> 00:05:20,614
This is not money. It's just cotton.

25
00:05:20,679 --> 00:05:23,096
You have spoilt my lakhs of rupees.

26
00:05:23,203 --> 00:05:26,679
You already have lakhs of rupees.
How much more do you want?

27
00:05:26,704 --> 00:05:29,662
Crores. I want to earn crores of rupees.

28
00:05:30,563 --> 00:05:33,551
You don't know what happens
to me when I see money.

29
00:05:34,319 --> 00:05:37,504
I feel ecstatic when I see money!

30
00:05:38,399 --> 00:05:40,252
My whole body starts to dance.

31
00:05:41,098 --> 00:05:44,341
I hear melodious music.

32
00:05:44,833 --> 00:05:46,803
Flowers blossom in my eyes.

33
00:05:47,518 --> 00:05:49,264
I can do anything for money.

34
00:05:49,398 --> 00:05:51,826
I can live, I can die.
I can sing. I can dance.

35
00:05:51,851 --> 00:05:53,493
- Can you take a bath?
- What?

36
00:05:53,555 --> 00:05:55,808
Can you take a bath?
The priest is about to come.

37
00:05:55,820 --> 00:05:58,749
The priest...
The priest is about to get some good news.

38
00:05:58,774 --> 00:06:01,170
The priest is about to get some good news.

39
00:06:03,156 --> 00:06:06,255
Hail Lakshmi [Goddess of wealth].

40
00:06:06,280 --> 00:06:08,892
Hail Lakshmi.

41
00:06:09,658 --> 00:06:13,407
Mother Lakshmi, your love for the owl,
your ride, very much...

42
00:06:14,210 --> 00:06:16,134
I am your greatest devotee.

43
00:06:16,731 --> 00:06:20,693
Please take care of your devotee.
Always stay with me.

44
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:22,919
Have a great time.

45
00:06:23,559 --> 00:06:26,100
Oh Mother, never leave me!

46
00:06:26,305 --> 00:06:27,367
Oh no. It has burnt too much.

47
00:06:27,492 --> 00:06:30,094
[CHANTING]

48
00:06:30,119 --> 00:06:33,629
Master, you've been burning the
same incense stick for five years.

49
00:06:33,839 --> 00:06:35,359
Why don't you buy some new sticks?

50
00:06:35,482 --> 00:06:38,067
No matter I use is for
five years or 50 years...

51
00:06:38,634 --> 00:06:41,927
Why do you have a problem when
Mother Lakshmi doesn't have any?

52
00:06:42,144 --> 00:06:44,812
Has the priest arrived?

53
00:06:44,930 --> 00:06:46,736
He is waiting for you.

54
00:06:47,327 --> 00:06:50,765
I have brought photographs of many girls.

55
00:06:50,790 --> 00:06:54,127
Keep them aside.
I don't care about their appearances.

56
00:06:54,221 --> 00:06:55,410
If she is blind, I will get her an eye.

57
00:06:55,443 --> 00:06:57,134
If she doesn't have a leg,
I'll get one Jaipur foot for her.

58
00:06:57,159 --> 00:06:58,777
If she's fat, I'll stop giving her food.

59
00:06:58,855 --> 00:07:01,087
Any girl would do, provided that...

60
00:07:01,167 --> 00:07:06,000
...she is the only daughter of
a millionaire father. Sit down.

61
00:07:06,119 --> 00:07:09,582
But at least their horoscopes should match.

62
00:07:09,607 --> 00:07:13,325
That's also not necessary,
but I should get the dowry.

63
00:07:13,502 --> 00:07:16,616
I have only one son.
I will get him married only once.

64
00:07:16,752 --> 00:07:19,049
So I want to get a good deal out of him.

65
00:07:19,209 --> 00:07:23,609
Hazari Prasad will do
this deal with utmost care.

66
00:07:23,638 --> 00:07:25,562
- Priest, here is tea for you.
- Thank you.

67
00:07:25,766 --> 00:07:29,347
You fool. Do you want to kill the priest?

68
00:07:29,368 --> 00:07:31,122
It's just tea, not poison.

69
00:07:31,159 --> 00:07:33,193
You fool, tea contains sugar.

70
00:07:33,218 --> 00:07:35,770
Sugar causes diabetes.
What if the priest dies due to diabetes?

71
00:07:35,811 --> 00:07:39,212
- I don't have any sugar problem.
- You may catch it.

72
00:07:39,233 --> 00:07:41,926
Why risk your life for just a cup of tea?

73
00:07:41,951 --> 00:07:44,238
- But I am ready to take the risk.
- But I won't let you drink.

74
00:07:44,295 --> 00:07:45,374
- I will drink.
- I won't let you drink.

75
00:07:45,403 --> 00:07:46,100
I will drink.

76
00:07:46,170 --> 00:07:47,125
There's a fly in the tea.

77
00:07:53,020 --> 00:07:56,260
See. Neither you got it, nor did I get it.

78
00:07:56,468 --> 00:07:57,796
The fly got it.

79
00:07:58,039 --> 00:08:03,739
Hazari Prasad will not waste this tea.

80
00:08:09,223 --> 00:08:10,881
Oh God!

81
00:08:12,068 --> 00:08:14,250
So what were you saying?

82
00:08:14,848 --> 00:08:19,233
I got your point,
but your son should also like the girl.

83
00:08:19,305 --> 00:08:21,623
You don't worry about my son.

84
00:08:22,533 --> 00:08:28,068
He is my blood.
The uniqueness of our family is...

85
00:08:28,671 --> 00:08:31,325
...we can lose anything, but not money.

86
00:09:07,316 --> 00:09:08,402
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

87
00:09:14,086 --> 00:09:16,123
Why are you misbehaving
with a helpless girl?

88
00:09:16,164 --> 00:09:17,423
I wasn't misbehaving.

89
00:09:18,933 --> 00:09:22,447
Well, she looks like my sister...

90
00:09:23,004 --> 00:09:27,265
- ...who passed away when she was born.
- So sad.

91
00:09:28,719 --> 00:09:33,823
Please tie this rakhi
[bond of sisterly love] to me.

92
00:09:34,511 --> 00:09:36,426
- Why not?! Sure.
- Thanks.

93
00:09:39,459 --> 00:09:42,206
Okay, Sister. Be in touch.

94
00:09:48,601 --> 00:09:49,757
[LAUGHING]

95
00:09:49,821 --> 00:09:53,365
You could have been
in huge trouble or else...

96
00:09:53,390 --> 00:09:55,712
Or else what? I have one policy.

97
00:09:56,153 --> 00:09:58,275
If she doesn't agree there
is always a rakhi ready.

98
00:09:58,312 --> 00:09:59,672
[LAUGHS]

99
00:09:59,699 --> 00:10:02,880
Let's go. We're getting late for college.

100
00:10:02,936 --> 00:10:03,873
- Oh yes.
- Come on, let's go.

101
00:10:07,333 --> 00:10:10,487
Raja! Is this the time to come to college?

102
00:10:11,411 --> 00:10:13,331
Answer me! Why are you silent?

103
00:10:17,955 --> 00:10:22,793
My father had a heart
attack for the fourth time.

104
00:10:22,876 --> 00:10:25,801
Oh my God!
You should have been in the hospital.

105
00:10:26,039 --> 00:10:27,963
But sir, what about the lectures,
my attendance...

106
00:10:27,998 --> 00:10:30,214
I will take care of all that.
Now go. Hurry up!

107
00:10:30,712 --> 00:10:33,112
- Thank you, sir.
- It's okay.

108
00:10:33,394 --> 00:10:34,964
- Thank you so much.
- Go.

109
00:10:36,540 --> 00:10:39,324
- Bye.
- What are you looking at?

110
00:10:39,349 --> 00:10:40,287
Go to your classes!

111
00:10:40,328 --> 00:10:41,662
- Sorry, sir.
- Go!

112
00:10:42,154 --> 00:10:44,996
LECTURER: <i>So as I told you, in Ohm's law...</i>

113
00:10:45,345 --> 00:10:47,121
<i>...the current flowing in a circuit...</i>

114
00:10:47,460 --> 00:10:51,942
<i>...is directly proportional to the
voltage and inversely proportional...</i>

115
00:10:51,967 --> 00:10:53,864
[BELL RINGING]

116
00:10:58,079 --> 00:11:02,400
Where are you going?
The lecture is not over.

117
00:11:02,570 --> 00:11:05,562
[CLAMOURING]

118
00:11:11,561 --> 00:11:14,534
Be silent. Silence.

119
00:11:15,194 --> 00:11:18,795
Friends, a storm had come
into this world 21 years ago.

120
00:11:19,039 --> 00:11:21,396
Tonight, again a storm is about to come.

121
00:11:21,714 --> 00:11:26,042
Tonight, you'll be flooded with beer.

122
00:11:26,386 --> 00:11:28,810
The world will shake with the dancing.

123
00:11:28,870 --> 00:11:33,824
Because today it's Raja's
birthday and you all are invited.

124
00:11:33,859 --> 00:11:35,593
[SHOUTS]

125
00:11:36,334 --> 00:11:38,550
[MUSIC PLAYING]

126
00:11:51,822 --> 00:11:54,777
Your bill for 200 chickens.

127
00:11:56,798 --> 00:12:00,642
Not Raja, but my dad, will pay the bill.

128
00:12:00,683 --> 00:12:01,685
[GLASS SHATTERS]

129
00:12:03,808 --> 00:12:08,499
"Father says I will make him proud."

130
00:12:08,680 --> 00:12:12,812
"My son will do something great."

131
00:12:12,873 --> 00:12:22,463
"But no one knows where my destination is."

132
00:12:23,839 --> 00:12:27,986
"I love to love you, baby."

133
00:12:28,431 --> 00:12:32,579
"I love to love you, baby."

134
00:12:33,037 --> 00:12:35,072
"Do it to me again and again."

135
00:12:35,152 --> 00:12:37,353
"Hey, come to me."

136
00:12:39,683 --> 00:12:43,753
"I love to love you, baby."

137
00:12:44,361 --> 00:12:47,736
- "I love to love you, baby."
- Move aside.

138
00:12:47,777 --> 00:12:49,313
Pandu, what's going on?

139
00:12:49,499 --> 00:12:51,534
Can't you see?! The party is going on.

140
00:12:51,639 --> 00:12:54,020
Okay, but where are you taking
these dry fruits?

141
00:12:54,122 --> 00:12:57,962
- It's for the guest.
- Give it to me.

142
00:12:59,114 --> 00:13:00,842
- You shouldn't eat it.
- Why?

143
00:13:01,703 --> 00:13:03,853
Because you may not be able to digest it.

144
00:13:03,914 --> 00:13:06,564
Whom did you call a dog?

145
00:13:21,293 --> 00:13:24,465
[SONG PLAYING]

146
00:13:46,638 --> 00:13:47,463
Silly.

147
00:13:48,342 --> 00:13:49,504
Who's that?

148
00:13:57,804 --> 00:14:01,250
[SONG PLAYING]

149
00:14:14,657 --> 00:14:17,616
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

150
00:14:44,760 --> 00:14:47,170
Hey, you. Look at this bill.

151
00:14:56,993 --> 00:14:59,360
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

152
00:15:05,096 --> 00:15:07,721
- Pay the bills.
- Pay the bills.

153
00:15:11,715 --> 00:15:13,594
[HUMMING]

154
00:15:18,315 --> 00:15:21,126
What did you do last night?

155
00:15:22,421 --> 00:15:23,798
Will your dad pay these bills?

156
00:15:23,888 --> 00:15:27,152
Of course, Dad. You need not ask me.
You pay the bills.

157
00:15:27,359 --> 00:15:29,273
How dare you talk to me like this?

158
00:15:29,298 --> 00:15:32,442
Why are you scolding him?

159
00:15:32,773 --> 00:15:37,160
He ruined me.
He spent Rs.20,000 in one night.

160
00:15:37,234 --> 00:15:39,532
You are wrong, it was not 20,000,
but it was 19,800.

161
00:15:39,557 --> 00:15:42,303
He doesn't throw parties regularly.

162
00:15:42,527 --> 00:15:44,021
Yesterday was his birthday.

163
00:15:44,070 --> 00:15:47,037
It was his birthday,
but it was doomsday for me.

164
00:15:47,612 --> 00:15:50,818
Ever since he was born,
he has celebrated his birthday 21 times.

165
00:15:51,540 --> 00:15:55,786
I earn money with so much hard work...

166
00:15:56,073 --> 00:15:58,955
...but you spend it so easily.

167
00:15:59,210 --> 00:16:00,868
You merciless person.

168
00:16:00,909 --> 00:16:04,547
You had too much money in your vault.

169
00:16:04,899 --> 00:16:07,702
I spent just a little. Move aside.

170
00:16:08,021 --> 00:16:10,399
- Are you searching for something?
- Keys for my bike.

171
00:16:10,593 --> 00:16:11,978
Hello, they are gone.

172
00:16:13,293 --> 00:16:16,212
- Where have they gone?
- With the motorcycle.

173
00:16:17,185 --> 00:16:18,823
- Where is my motorcycle?
- I sold it.

174
00:16:19,034 --> 00:16:22,348
- You sold it! Why?
- To pay the bills.

175
00:16:22,473 --> 00:16:24,573
How will I go to college?

176
00:16:25,095 --> 00:16:27,720
Just like Mahatma Gandhi went
to Dhandi from Sabarmati. On foot!

177
00:16:27,862 --> 00:16:29,887
- What have you done?
- Nothing.

178
00:16:30,340 --> 00:16:32,449
I have shown him what
the whole world knows.

179
00:16:32,573 --> 00:16:35,244
- What?
- That I am your father.

180
00:16:37,788 --> 00:16:39,332
[LAUGHS]

181
00:16:39,954 --> 00:16:42,172
We had a lot of fun
at your party last night.

182
00:16:42,203 --> 00:16:45,540
- Your father is a great person.
- Don't talk about my father.

183
00:16:49,163 --> 00:16:50,084
Are you blind?

184
00:16:50,144 --> 00:16:51,671
[TYRES SCREECHING]

185
00:17:02,503 --> 00:17:03,511
[TYRES SCREECHING]

186
00:17:04,127 --> 00:17:07,359
Has your father brought
this road along with the car?

187
00:17:07,716 --> 00:17:11,412
Hey, mister!
Why don't you look before you walk?

188
00:17:11,958 --> 00:17:15,553
Don't you know how to walk on the road?
Fool!

189
00:17:15,730 --> 00:17:16,446
Idiot.

190
00:17:16,737 --> 00:17:17,885
Hey!

191
00:17:23,293 --> 00:17:27,028
She's just too much!

192
00:17:27,324 --> 00:17:29,376
She looks like a newcomer.

193
00:17:29,401 --> 00:17:31,556
She's as proud as she is beautiful.

194
00:17:31,919 --> 00:17:36,606
She's just too hot!

195
00:17:37,042 --> 00:17:37,737
[GASPING]

196
00:17:37,993 --> 00:17:42,838
Tomorrow I'll teach her a lesson.

197
00:17:48,057 --> 00:17:49,214
[HORN HONKING]

198
00:17:51,893 --> 00:17:53,011
[TYRES SCREECHING]

199
00:17:54,821 --> 00:17:56,665
Can't you see where you are walking?
Are you blind?

200
00:17:58,660 --> 00:18:00,100
Can somebody help me?

201
00:18:00,587 --> 00:18:03,007
Oh my God, he's really blind.

202
00:18:03,780 --> 00:18:05,107
My books.

203
00:18:05,975 --> 00:18:07,389
My stick!

204
00:18:10,001 --> 00:18:10,763
Listen.

205
00:18:11,156 --> 00:18:12,250
- Here is your stick.
- Who?

206
00:18:12,701 --> 00:18:14,163
Did you get hurt?

207
00:18:16,098 --> 00:18:18,929
The Lord has already disabled me for life.

208
00:18:19,632 --> 00:18:21,176
These things don't hurt me anymore.

209
00:18:22,041 --> 00:18:23,314
It's not your fault.

210
00:18:24,251 --> 00:18:27,575
It's a big mistake to be born blind.

211
00:18:28,064 --> 00:18:30,080
Don't say that.

212
00:18:30,252 --> 00:18:32,836
Shall I drop you somewhere?

213
00:18:33,272 --> 00:18:35,241
It doesn't matter to a blind man...

214
00:18:35,660 --> 00:18:37,641
...whether he is coming or going somewhere.

215
00:18:37,986 --> 00:18:40,279
God has already taken my eyes.

216
00:18:40,809 --> 00:18:44,264
I was going to college
to enlighten my mind.

217
00:18:44,973 --> 00:18:50,156
For your information, I study in
the blind section of G.K. College.

218
00:18:50,641 --> 00:18:53,919
- G.K. College! I also study there.
- Really.

219
00:18:53,993 --> 00:18:55,281
Come on, I'll drop you there.

220
00:18:55,382 --> 00:18:57,517
No. I don't want to give you any trouble.

221
00:18:57,588 --> 00:19:01,078
- Please come with me.
- Okay.

222
00:19:04,841 --> 00:19:05,813
Be careful.

223
00:19:07,273 --> 00:19:09,717
- On which floor is your class?
- Class!

224
00:19:12,003 --> 00:19:12,858
Be careful!

225
00:19:13,928 --> 00:19:15,333
- I am sorry.
- It's okay.

226
00:19:15,479 --> 00:19:18,317
- Keep your hand on my shoulder.
- Okay.

227
00:19:19,756 --> 00:19:22,233
Really,
you are taking a lot of trouble for me.

228
00:19:22,273 --> 00:19:23,467
No.

229
00:19:24,213 --> 00:19:25,844
Today you have helped a blind person.

230
00:19:26,476 --> 00:19:28,559
You are a very nice girl. Ouch!

231
00:19:30,137 --> 00:19:32,489
Life has been unjust to you.

232
00:19:33,127 --> 00:19:34,822
Sometimes God...

233
00:19:35,304 --> 00:19:37,968
[LAUGHS]

234
00:19:49,859 --> 00:19:50,694
Who are you?

235
00:19:51,866 --> 00:19:54,870
Dev Anand is my name.

236
00:19:56,095 --> 00:19:56,856
Shut up!

237
00:19:59,199 --> 00:20:02,217
'For those who hate me,
I will fill their hearts with love.'

238
00:20:02,315 --> 00:20:05,417
'I am the person who can soften a rock.'

239
00:20:05,920 --> 00:20:06,965
Get lost.

240
00:20:11,176 --> 00:20:12,527
You fool.

241
00:20:15,660 --> 00:20:19,419
'The way she collided against me.'

242
00:20:20,085 --> 00:20:23,324
'I swear I enjoyed it.'

243
00:20:23,349 --> 00:20:25,255
[LAUGHS]

244
00:20:29,981 --> 00:20:31,123
Who the hell are you?

245
00:20:33,881 --> 00:20:37,392
I'm the one on whom you had
splashed muddy water yesterday.

246
00:20:38,174 --> 00:20:39,904
Yesterday I had just spoilt your face.

247
00:20:40,672 --> 00:20:43,805
But today,
I will redden your face with my sandal.

248
00:21:17,007 --> 00:21:19,594
"Arrogant is her stance."

249
00:21:19,635 --> 00:21:22,176
"She's a girl or a cane?"

250
00:21:22,258 --> 00:21:24,738
"She is fire. She is a banger."

251
00:21:24,876 --> 00:21:26,961
"She's a cracker of a girl."

252
00:21:27,021 --> 00:21:28,729
"Anger in her eyes."

253
00:21:29,609 --> 00:21:31,413
"Always ready with abuses."

254
