504
00:39:23,479 --> 00:39:24,515
[PANTING]

505
00:39:28,882 --> 00:39:31,543
Miss. Madhu, please come. Welcome.

506
00:39:31,584 --> 00:39:33,637
Friends, give her a big hand.

507
00:39:33,678 --> 00:39:37,114
[CHEERING]

508
00:40:35,887 --> 00:40:37,839
When I was younger I was taught...

509
00:40:38,886 --> 00:40:41,734
...to always stay away
from unimportant people.

510
00:40:43,617 --> 00:40:46,028
[CHEERING]

511
00:40:46,069 --> 00:40:50,446
Raja! Raja! Raja! Raja!
[CROWD WHISTLING]

512
00:40:50,487 --> 00:40:58,291
Raja! Raja! Raja! Raja!

513
00:41:05,582 --> 00:41:07,648
No.

514
00:41:13,190 --> 00:41:14,879
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

515
00:41:15,655 --> 00:41:18,682
- Son, are you going to the temple?
- Yes, Mother.

516
00:41:19,690 --> 00:41:22,108
Have you thought about Madhu?

517
00:41:22,140 --> 00:41:23,912
That's why I am going to the temple.

518
00:41:24,455 --> 00:41:26,874
I am going to request God
to do something about her...

519
00:41:26,965 --> 00:41:27,799
...and I'll also try to do my bit.

520
00:41:28,132 --> 00:41:29,519
But where is Madhu?

521
00:41:31,255 --> 00:41:34,355
- There you are.
- Daddy, I want a goli [bullet].

522
00:41:34,582 --> 00:41:37,684
Didn't Ramu give you the vitamin goli?

523
00:41:37,741 --> 00:41:41,316
- I need a bullet.
- Bullet!

524
00:41:41,391 --> 00:41:42,503
What happened?

525
00:41:42,528 --> 00:41:44,498
I will kill that scum.

526
00:41:44,938 --> 00:41:48,495
Until I shoot him,
I won't have my breakfast.

527
00:41:48,750 --> 00:41:49,871
What happened?

528
00:41:50,078 --> 00:41:53,233
He insulted me in front of everyone.

529
00:41:53,386 --> 00:41:54,579
Insulted you?! How?

530
00:41:55,121 --> 00:41:56,712
He held me in front of everyone...

531
00:41:56,784 --> 00:41:58,316
What did he do to you?

532
00:41:59,848 --> 00:42:00,975
He did nothing.

533
00:42:01,119 --> 00:42:04,372
He did nothing? Then how were you insulted?

534
00:42:04,791 --> 00:42:07,115
- Let her speak.
- Good morning, Uncle.

535
00:42:07,304 --> 00:42:09,346
- Hello.
- Greetings, grandma.

536
00:42:09,387 --> 00:42:10,292
- Greetings!
- Hi!

537
00:42:10,642 --> 00:42:12,186
What happened to you?

538
00:42:12,800 --> 00:42:15,062
- Are you alright?
- I am absolutely fine.

539
00:42:15,175 --> 00:42:17,030
But your lips look swollen.

540
00:42:17,071 --> 00:42:20,160
No, sir. The thing is...

541
00:42:20,614 --> 00:42:21,223
[CHUCKLES]

542
00:42:22,408 --> 00:42:24,699
...I'm boxing a bit too much.

543
00:42:25,265 --> 00:42:27,952
Don't box so much...

544
00:42:28,146 --> 00:42:29,773
...or else it will be
hard to recognise you.

545
00:42:29,912 --> 00:42:31,227
When is your father
coming back from London?

546
00:42:31,363 --> 00:42:32,918
- Next week.
- Next week!

547
00:42:32,959 --> 00:42:34,655
I forgot. I had to go to the temple.

548
00:42:34,735 --> 00:42:37,102
- You keep talking. I am leaving.
- Ok.

549
00:42:37,565 --> 00:42:38,627
[TEMPLE BELL]

550
00:42:39,033 --> 00:42:41,243
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

551
00:42:45,357 --> 00:42:46,384
Take it.

552
00:42:47,119 --> 00:42:48,575
Hail to you.

553
00:42:50,044 --> 00:42:51,490
- God bless you.
- Be happy.

554
00:42:51,522 --> 00:42:53,350
Our saviour is here.

555
00:42:53,379 --> 00:42:55,535
- Our Almighty is here.
- He is here.

556
00:42:55,692 --> 00:42:57,095
Our God is here.

557
00:42:57,120 --> 00:43:01,626
Our God is here. Long live our master.

558
00:43:01,651 --> 00:43:04,170
- Get up.
- God bless you.

559
00:43:04,334 --> 00:43:06,818
- Greetings.
- Who is he?

560
00:43:06,892 --> 00:43:08,551
He looks like a reincarnation of God.

561
00:43:08,592 --> 00:43:11,143
- Please sit, everyone will get it.
- Sit down. Don't rush.

562
00:43:11,771 --> 00:43:13,749
- Take this.
- Sit quietly.

563
00:43:13,790 --> 00:43:15,447
- He'll give you, sit quietly.
- You take it as well.

564
00:43:16,673 --> 00:43:17,775
Take this.

565
00:43:19,813 --> 00:43:22,579
What would've happened to us
if you had not been there for us?

566
00:43:22,846 --> 00:43:26,150
I think that I am poorer than you.

567
00:43:26,651 --> 00:43:28,092
God has given me so much money...

568
00:43:28,117 --> 00:43:30,229
...but he has given me
just two hands to give.

569
00:43:30,497 --> 00:43:34,116
I wish he'd have given
me 1,000 hands to donate.

570
00:43:34,534 --> 00:43:35,845
[SOBBING]

571
00:43:36,034 --> 00:43:37,598
God bless you!

572
00:43:41,073 --> 00:43:42,136
[TEMPLE BELL]

573
00:43:45,676 --> 00:43:50,923
Mother Goddess,
you have given me so much wealth.

574
00:43:51,453 --> 00:43:54,872
But still,
I come to you everyday as a beggar.

575
00:43:55,377 --> 00:43:56,415
I beg to you.

576
00:43:57,181 --> 00:43:59,079
The way you have given me so much wealth...

577
00:43:59,599 --> 00:44:01,411
...give me a good daughter-in-law.

578
00:44:02,065 --> 00:44:03,970
I don't want anything else.

579
00:44:04,763 --> 00:44:07,404
I just want a good daughter-in-law.

580
00:44:08,243 --> 00:44:11,409
Mother. Give me a good daughter-in-law.

581
00:44:11,690 --> 00:44:15,257
Give me a good daughter-in-law.

582
00:44:22,856 --> 00:44:23,473
[HISSING]

583
00:44:23,736 --> 00:44:25,107
Yes, sir.

584
00:44:25,641 --> 00:44:27,037
- Go.
- Yes, sir.

585
00:44:28,174 --> 00:44:29,086
Mother.

586
00:44:33,737 --> 00:44:34,908
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

587
00:44:40,575 --> 00:44:43,503
- The tyres have been punctured.
- Don't you have any spare tyres?

588
00:44:43,630 --> 00:44:45,661
We have only one spare tyre,
but two tyres are punctured.

589
00:44:45,802 --> 00:44:49,036
I had such an important meeting
and there is no phone around...

590
00:44:49,061 --> 00:44:51,044
If you don't mind, I can give you a lift.

591
00:44:51,108 --> 00:44:53,757
- I will drop you wherever you want.
- Don't trouble yourself.

592
00:44:54,415 --> 00:44:56,948
Take this. Give us a sandwich.

593
00:44:57,475 --> 00:44:59,523
A Rs.100 note.
How did you get a Rs.100 note?

594
00:44:59,655 --> 00:45:02,034
- Why do you care?
- Okay.

595
00:45:04,045 --> 00:45:06,715
This is a fake currency note.

596
00:45:06,794 --> 00:45:10,886
Take it away.
I'll take you to the police. Go away.

597
00:45:10,942 --> 00:45:13,492
- A fake note? Ramu.
- Mine is also a fake note.

598
00:45:13,615 --> 00:45:14,216
Your?

599
00:45:14,257 --> 00:45:16,154
- Mine, too.
- Where is that man?

600
00:45:16,385 --> 00:45:19,082
- There's no problem at all. Please come.
- There he is.

601
00:45:19,108 --> 00:45:20,790
It's very sweet of you.
Thank you very much. God bless you.

602
00:45:20,949 --> 00:45:22,101
Catch him!

603
00:45:24,486 --> 00:45:26,740
You gave us fake notes. You fooled us.

604
00:45:26,781 --> 00:45:27,968
Goodbye.

605
00:45:29,775 --> 00:45:31,657
They love you a lot.

606
00:45:32,882 --> 00:45:35,356
They respect you more than God.

607
00:45:35,415 --> 00:45:37,005
It's just their affection.

608
00:45:37,426 --> 00:45:40,411
No one can become a God by
donating some 10 to 20 lakhs.

609
00:45:40,601 --> 00:45:42,085
Drive faster.

610
00:45:42,188 --> 00:45:45,210
Beat him! Catch him! Don't let him escape!

611
00:45:47,927 --> 00:45:50,170
He made a fool of us.
He gave us fake notes.

612
00:45:50,195 --> 00:45:54,356
- If I get him, I will break his teeth.
- Beat him!

613
00:45:54,452 --> 00:45:56,340
- By the way, I am Mehra.
- I am also...

614
00:45:56,365 --> 00:45:59,082
I mean, I am Hazari Prasad.

615
00:45:59,690 --> 00:46:02,467
I haven't seen you before.
Are you new in this city?

616
00:46:02,783 --> 00:46:07,657
No. I belong to this place,
but I left this place to earn money.

617
00:46:08,405 --> 00:46:10,786
By the way, which business are you in?

618
00:46:11,049 --> 00:46:13,573
Nothing really.
I have some textile mills...

619
00:46:13,692 --> 00:46:16,077
...some shipping corporations,
some chemical industries.

620
00:46:16,118 --> 00:46:19,333
- That's it. I'm a small businessman.
- Small businessman!

621
00:46:19,604 --> 00:46:21,385
You have a very good sense of humour.

622
00:46:22,146 --> 00:46:23,274
MEHRA: What are
you doing this evening?

623
00:46:23,298 --> 00:46:24,537
HAZARI PRASAD: Nothing
really. Whatever you say.

624
00:46:24,628 --> 00:46:26,162
- MEHRA: Let's have drinks together.
- HAZARI PRASAD: Sure.

625
00:46:26,634 --> 00:46:29,556
MEHRA: Let's meet and have a drink.

626
00:46:44,653 --> 00:46:46,723
Cheers! Long live our friendship.

627
00:46:46,940 --> 00:46:48,200
In the name of friendship.

628
00:46:53,161 --> 00:46:55,304
Where is Mr. Mehra?

629
00:46:55,487 --> 00:46:56,944
He is very punctual.

630
00:46:57,823 --> 00:47:00,149
He comes at 9 everyday.
I don't know why he is late today.

631
00:47:01,269 --> 00:47:02,465
Mr. Mehra has arrived.

632
00:47:02,506 --> 00:47:03,701
- Good morning, sir.
- Good morning.

633
00:47:04,778 --> 00:47:06,279
- Do you remember all your dialogues?
- Yes.

634
00:47:06,357 --> 00:47:07,577
- Then let's get started.
- Yes.

635
00:47:07,750 --> 00:47:10,101
What do you think of yourself?

636
00:47:10,249 --> 00:47:14,474
Do you think I'm an immoral, greedy,
and unethical person? Go away.

637
00:47:14,573 --> 00:47:16,684
What's the matter, Hazari Prasad?
You seem to be very upset.

638
00:47:16,938 --> 00:47:18,397
What can I say?

639
00:47:18,438 --> 00:47:22,124
I told this priest so many times that
I just want a good daughter-in-law...

640
00:47:22,283 --> 00:47:24,690
...even if she is poor.

641
00:47:25,457 --> 00:47:27,220
But this priest comes along with...

642
00:47:27,245 --> 00:47:29,264
...the proposals of
millionaires and billionaires.

643
00:47:29,775 --> 00:47:31,353
They want to buy my son.

644
00:47:31,581 --> 00:47:34,429
Money cannot create character and virtues.

645
00:47:35,002 --> 00:47:37,004
But this fool doesn't understand.

646
00:47:37,057 --> 00:47:38,865
Shall I say something?

647
00:47:39,464 --> 00:47:41,441
Yes, definitely. I'll not feel bad.

648
00:47:41,465 --> 00:47:42,651
This is your right.

649
00:47:43,629 --> 00:47:47,377
I know a girl who is suitable
to be your daughter-in-law.

650
00:47:47,765 --> 00:47:49,490
Who is that girl? Where is she?

651
00:47:49,515 --> 00:47:51,799
I'll be indebted to you forever.

652
00:47:52,715 --> 00:47:53,951
She is my daughter.

653
00:47:56,375 --> 00:47:57,765
- Your daughter?
- Yes!

654
00:47:59,580 --> 00:48:02,957
Why are you silent? This was
just my opinion. I am not forcing you.

655
00:48:03,917 --> 00:48:07,650
Our friendship is over.

656
00:48:10,199 --> 00:48:13,288
Because we are not friends anymore,
but relatives.

657
00:48:16,745 --> 00:48:17,607
[SIGHS]

658
00:48:17,676 --> 00:48:18,879
[LAUGHS]

659
00:48:19,118 --> 00:48:20,870
You have such a great sense of humour.

660
00:48:20,958 --> 00:48:22,964
Isn't it bizarre that the girl
was right here under my nose...

661
00:48:23,215 --> 00:48:25,279
...and I was looking all over the place?

662
00:48:25,497 --> 00:48:27,370
Match the horoscopes.

663
00:48:27,501 --> 00:48:30,009
Everything will match after that.
I hope you got it.

664
00:48:30,034 --> 00:48:33,292
Yes, sir.
Give me your daughter's horoscope.

665
00:48:33,448 --> 00:48:34,581
I don't have her horoscope.

666
00:48:34,865 --> 00:48:36,823
Then tell me her time,
date and year of birth.

667
00:48:36,879 --> 00:48:41,402
I remember it very well.
8th January, 1971 in the winter.

668
00:48:41,427 --> 00:48:42,909
- That's okay.
- Write it.

669
00:48:46,291 --> 00:48:47,854
[MUMBLE]

670
00:48:47,879 --> 00:48:52,379
Jupiter is in the eleventh place.
It matches! Wow!

671
00:48:52,437 --> 00:48:56,426
Congratulations!
Such matching horoscopes are rare to find.

672
00:48:56,451 --> 00:48:58,628
All the qualities and
virtues match perfectly.

673
00:48:58,872 --> 00:49:03,184
Only the horoscopes of Gods and
Goddesses used to match this way.

674
00:49:03,209 --> 00:49:05,579
Now,
Raja and Madhu's horoscopes have matched.

675
00:49:05,673 --> 00:49:08,183
It's fantastic!

676
00:49:08,674 --> 00:49:11,934
[MUSIC PLAYING]

677
00:50:15,599 --> 00:50:19,299
[MUSIC PLAYING]

678
00:50:29,887 --> 00:50:30,716
Shut up!

679
00:50:33,750 --> 00:50:34,989
What do you think of yourself?

680
00:50:39,938 --> 00:50:40,508
Single.

681
00:50:40,533 --> 00:50:41,810
[LAUGHS]

682
00:50:41,888 --> 00:50:43,803
It's very easy to laugh at others.

683
00:50:44,001 --> 00:50:45,598
If you are a real man, then dance with me.

684
00:50:45,638 --> 00:50:48,538
I have told you before,
I don't mess with girls.

685
00:50:49,500 --> 00:50:51,630
Only a real man can.

686
00:51:03,097 --> 00:51:04,034
Greetings, sir.

687
00:51:04,182 --> 00:51:05,181
- Greetings.
- Please, come.

688
00:51:05,237 --> 00:51:06,229
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

689
00:51:08,311 --> 00:51:10,575
- Please sit. Mr. Mehra will be here soon.
- Okay.

690
00:51:11,542 --> 00:51:12,557
Where have you brought me?

691
00:51:12,582 --> 00:51:16,239
Don't mess up. I have worked
very hard for this. Don't destroy it.

692
00:51:16,515 --> 00:51:18,872
How can I marry a girl
whom I have never seen?

693
00:51:18,897 --> 00:51:20,920
- Just the way I did.
- I won't do it.

694
00:51:20,945 --> 00:51:22,080
- I will slap you.
- I will shout.

695
00:51:22,096 --> 00:51:24,856
- Shut up, you fool!
- MEHRA: Hello, Hazari Prasad.

696
00:51:24,942 --> 00:51:28,515
- My son.
- You two seem pretty close.

697
00:51:28,700 --> 00:51:32,215
I felt like hugging my son. My dear!

698
00:51:33,183 --> 00:51:34,062
She is my mother.

699
00:51:34,102 --> 00:51:34,758
- Greetings!
- Greetings!

700
00:51:34,838 --> 00:51:36,856
- This is my son, Raja.
- God bless you. Sit down.

701
00:51:37,165 --> 00:51:38,890
Where is your daughter?

702
00:51:38,931 --> 00:51:40,860
She took Chinky out for a walk.
She will be here in a moment.

703
00:51:40,901 --> 00:51:41,681
[DOG BARKING]

704
00:51:41,771 --> 00:51:44,479
- Hi, Daddy.
- Hi, dear. Come.

705
00:51:44,890 --> 00:51:46,878
He is Mr. Hazari Prasad your
future father-in-law... - Hello.

706
00:51:46,919 --> 00:51:47,509
Hi!

707
00:51:48,191 --> 00:51:50,050
- That's his son.
- Son.

708
00:51:51,955 --> 00:51:53,469
- You!
- You!

709
00:51:53,730 --> 00:51:55,284
Do you know each other?

710
00:51:55,325 --> 00:51:58,743
Do you want me to marry this guy?
This fool!

711
00:51:58,815 --> 00:52:00,544
I won't even allow Chinky
to get married to him.

712
00:52:00,569 --> 00:52:03,705
I am ready to marry this dog, but not you.

713
00:52:03,744 --> 00:52:04,173
[GASPS]

714
00:52:04,198 --> 00:52:06,047
- Do you want me to marry this witch?
- Witch!

715
00:52:06,088 --> 00:52:07,344
- Am I a witch?
- Very good.

716
00:52:07,375 --> 00:52:10,399
Since you two know each
other so well why the delay?

717
00:52:10,455 --> 00:52:12,255
- Congratulations, Mr. Mehra.
- Shut up!

718
00:52:12,295 --> 00:52:15,243
- Don't insult my father.
- What are you doing?

719
00:52:15,475 --> 00:52:19,456
You don't know him. He's scum.

720
00:52:19,520 --> 00:52:21,360
Yes and you are a very good girl!

721
00:52:21,385 --> 00:52:24,961
Why are you spoiling everything?
Keep quiet.

722
00:52:25,002 --> 00:52:26,957
Move aside, Daddy.
I will deal with this lizard.

723
00:52:26,998 --> 00:52:29,621
- Lizard!
- You called me a lizard!

724
00:52:29,662 --> 00:52:32,576
Daddy, get aside. You cockroach!

725
00:52:33,508 --> 00:52:34,663
Take this!

726
00:52:40,097 --> 00:52:43,051
You did this to my father!
I won't spare you.

727
00:52:43,615 --> 00:52:44,419
Take this.

728
00:52:49,321 --> 00:52:51,297
A cake for a cake.

729
00:52:51,338 --> 00:52:54,219
- Why are you taking revenge on me?
- You have insulted my father.

730
00:52:54,541 --> 00:52:55,975
You swine!

731
00:52:56,015 --> 00:52:58,077
Dear, listen to me.

732
00:52:58,118 --> 00:53:00,172
Hey, dear. Control her.

733
00:53:00,288 --> 00:53:01,333
You little rat!

734
00:53:01,375 --> 00:53:04,009
- RAJA: You can't harm me in any ways.
- Leave me, dad.

735
00:53:04,034 --> 00:53:06,358
- Go away, you witch!
- How dare you?

736
00:53:06,415 --> 00:53:08,502
- I will deal with you.
- I will not spare him.

737
00:53:08,534 --> 00:53:10,648
- He called me a lizard.
- Let go off me!

738
00:53:10,673 --> 00:53:14,540
Let go of me, Daddy. You have
been insulted. I will not stay here.

739
00:53:14,655 --> 00:53:16,539
- I'm leaving.
- Stop, son.

740
00:53:16,580 --> 00:53:19,170
Hazari, how can this happen to you?
Mr. Mehra.

741
00:53:21,892 --> 00:53:24,243
I am dead. Save me.

742
00:53:25,166 --> 00:53:26,299
[WATER SPLASHES]

743
00:53:29,130 --> 00:53:33,270
[GROANING]

744
00:53:34,519 --> 00:53:38,042
I will die? I won't stay alive!

745
00:53:38,229 --> 00:53:40,433
My last days are here.

746
00:53:40,802 --> 00:53:44,342
My son will be solely
responsible for my death.

747
00:53:44,367 --> 00:53:48,262
Control yourself or else
your health will deteriorate.

748
00:53:48,505 --> 00:53:50,471
It can't get worse than this.

749
00:53:50,752 --> 00:53:52,370
Lift it a bit.

750
00:53:52,395 --> 00:53:53,336
[SOBBING]

751
00:53:53,419 --> 00:53:55,735
