I am not only her father,
but also her mother.

1011
01:17:16,930 --> 01:17:19,984
I hope you know it's so
difficult to be a mother.

1012
01:17:20,220 --> 01:17:23,038
I am giving you the most
precious of my belongings.

1013
01:17:23,332 --> 01:17:28,885
I will take utmost care of her.
This is a promise.

1014
01:17:28,980 --> 01:17:31,820
- Congrats, Mr. Mehra.
- Mahesh.

1015
01:17:31,955 --> 01:17:33,462
Congratulations on your
daughter's engagement.

1016
01:17:33,503 --> 01:17:34,624
- Thank you.
- Congratulations.

1017
01:17:34,665 --> 01:17:36,506
- But I do regret one thing.
- What?

1018
01:17:36,817 --> 01:17:39,490
- We could not become relatives.
- That is...

1019
01:17:39,629 --> 01:17:42,052
Shakti and Madhu were
friends since childhood.

1020
01:17:42,077 --> 01:17:42,971
Of course.

1021
01:17:43,035 --> 01:17:44,567
That's why I regret it.

1022
01:17:44,608 --> 01:17:46,878
- Anyway, I heartily congratulate you.
- Thank you.

1023
01:17:47,031 --> 01:17:48,226
Go and get yourself a drink.

1024
01:17:48,267 --> 01:17:49,717
- Shakti, you too.
- Yes.

1025
01:17:49,758 --> 01:17:53,041
Hey, Girdhari!
Come, I will introduce you to a friend.

1026
01:17:53,478 --> 01:17:55,980
Girdhari!

1027
01:17:56,247 --> 01:17:57,831
Mehra!

1028
01:17:59,710 --> 01:18:02,186
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

1029
01:18:08,795 --> 01:18:10,030
What are you staring at?

1030
01:18:10,755 --> 01:18:12,785
He is the groom's father, Hazari Prasad.

1031
01:18:12,835 --> 01:18:15,875
He is a very old friend of mine,
Girdharilal.

1032
01:18:15,904 --> 01:18:17,171
- Greetings.
- Hello.

1033
01:18:17,412 --> 01:18:20,185
I think that I have seen you before.

1034
01:18:20,512 --> 01:18:23,369
You must have seen me at
an inauguration ceremony.

1035
01:18:23,432 --> 01:18:24,930
He is not as he seems.

1036
01:18:25,241 --> 01:18:27,651
He appears very simple,
but he is something else.

1037
01:18:27,692 --> 01:18:30,764
I should take care of other guests.

1038
01:18:30,805 --> 01:18:32,633
- Excuse me.
- Sure.

1039
01:18:35,528 --> 01:18:37,994
Have you properly enquired about him?

1040
01:18:38,035 --> 01:18:40,557
Why should I? He has textile mills.

1041
01:18:40,775 --> 01:18:43,121
He has chemical factories.
He has a construction business.

1042
01:18:43,236 --> 01:18:44,455
He is rich man.

1043
01:19:05,518 --> 01:19:09,588
- Have one drink with me.
- Definitely. We shall!

1044
01:19:10,234 --> 01:19:11,593
Hey, brother. Shall we?

1045
01:19:13,704 --> 01:19:14,588
Hello!

1046
01:19:16,022 --> 01:19:18,620
Tell me. When will I get married?

1047
01:19:20,011 --> 01:19:21,379
Quickly.

1048
01:19:24,952 --> 01:19:27,479
'The whole world will see and so will you.'

1049
01:19:27,520 --> 01:19:32,340
'I will get my son married
to a millionaire's daughter.'

1050
01:19:42,915 --> 01:19:44,387
What a cute child.

1051
01:19:44,595 --> 01:19:45,900
- How is the drink?
- Fine.

1052
01:19:45,956 --> 01:19:47,714
Excuse me. Mehra, come here.

1053
01:19:48,635 --> 01:19:49,592
- Mehra.
- Yes?

1054
01:19:49,666 --> 01:19:50,620
I just remembered that...

1055
01:19:50,755 --> 01:19:53,475
You remember everything after two pegs.

1056
01:19:53,519 --> 01:19:56,120
I am not kidding. I am serious.

1057
01:19:56,141 --> 01:19:58,055
If you care about your
daughter's welfare...

1058
01:19:58,076 --> 01:19:59,912
...then call off this
engagement immediately.

1059
01:20:00,260 --> 01:20:01,404
- Call off the engagement!
- Yes.

1060
01:20:01,445 --> 01:20:03,210
- Are you in your senses?
- Yes, I am...

1061
01:20:03,235 --> 01:20:06,942
...but until you come to your senses,
Hazari Prasad will have looted you.

1062
01:20:07,110 --> 01:20:11,105
- What are you saying?
- Yes, he doesn't have any mills.

1063
01:20:11,236 --> 01:20:15,946
He is not a millionaire,
but a junk-shop owner.

1064
01:20:16,050 --> 01:20:17,412
- What?
- Yes.

1065
01:20:17,714 --> 01:20:21,331
[MUSIC PLAYING]

1066
01:20:51,875 --> 01:20:54,159
Actually, he is a junk-shop owner.

1067
01:21:04,571 --> 01:21:07,834
[APPLAUSE]

1068
01:21:07,875 --> 01:21:11,389
At a party in 1947 when I
danced with Madhubala...

1069
01:21:11,430 --> 01:21:13,317
...people kept watching.

1070
01:21:13,365 --> 01:21:17,973
I think we should go ahead
with the engagement ceremony.

1071
01:21:18,515 --> 01:21:19,815
The auspicious time will pass by.

1072
01:21:19,878 --> 01:21:24,886
I also think so. The engagement
should take place immediately.

1073
01:21:24,927 --> 01:21:27,553
The auspicious time is passing by.
Call Raja and Madhu.

1074
01:21:27,578 --> 01:21:28,748
They will come.

1075
01:21:28,865 --> 01:21:32,044
But I want to introduce
you to some of my guests.

1076
01:21:32,167 --> 01:21:35,212
- No! I...
- Come.

1077
01:21:36,083 --> 01:21:36,817
Come on.

1078
01:21:39,677 --> 01:21:45,004
Friends, I am very happy
to see all of you here.

1079
01:21:45,633 --> 01:21:47,633
Before the engagement takes place...

1080
01:21:47,998 --> 01:21:49,935
...I'd like to introduce you to...

1081
01:21:50,366 --> 01:21:52,824
...to the groom's father,
Mr. Hazari Prasad.

1082
01:21:54,737 --> 01:21:56,092
He is a very unique person.

1083
01:21:57,184 --> 01:22:03,070
It will take too long to
speak about his greatness.

1084
01:22:03,927 --> 01:22:05,808
Mr. Mehra, you are flattering me.

1085
01:22:05,940 --> 01:22:08,666
We can do this after the engagement.
The auspicious time is passing.

1086
01:22:08,687 --> 01:22:11,456
The time has arrived now. Just two minutes.

1087
01:22:12,908 --> 01:22:18,769
Friends, Mr. Hazari Prasad who
has many chemical factories...

1088
01:22:19,183 --> 01:22:21,489
...who has many textile mills...

1089
01:22:21,530 --> 01:22:25,063
...and who is one of the
richest people in this city.

1090
01:22:26,043 --> 01:22:31,348
In reality, he is a cheap junk-shop owner.

1091
01:22:32,395 --> 01:22:33,683
A junk-shop owner.

1092
01:22:35,195 --> 01:22:40,022
The junk...
where we sell our old newspapers!

1093
01:22:41,143 --> 01:22:46,522
Where we sell the old bottles,
torn clothes.

1094
01:22:46,629 --> 01:22:50,691
Broken furniture.
These are the things he sells.

1095
01:22:50,816 --> 01:22:53,743
How dare...

1096
01:22:54,832 --> 01:22:58,091
...he dream of becoming
my daughter's father-in-law?

1097
01:22:58,132 --> 01:23:01,628
You are insulting me in front of everyone.

1098
01:23:01,669 --> 01:23:05,559
Insult! Only those get insulted
who have some self-respect.

1099
01:23:05,706 --> 01:23:07,214
- You have none.
- Mehra!

1100
01:23:07,300 --> 01:23:09,850
Shut your mouth!

1101
01:23:11,894 --> 01:23:14,194
And listen more about this fraudster!

1102
01:23:14,577 --> 01:23:19,604
This conman wanted to
take away my wealth in dowry.

1103
01:23:19,749 --> 01:23:21,115
So that I become penniless.

1104
01:23:21,140 --> 01:23:23,479
- Mehra, if you say one more word, then...
- Then!

1105
01:23:40,049 --> 01:23:41,764
Daddy, what have you done?

1106
01:23:41,998 --> 01:23:44,996
He was going to ruin us.

1107
01:23:45,037 --> 01:23:49,021
Thank God,
your life was saved from being destroyed.

1108
01:23:50,435 --> 01:23:53,661
This world will change.

1109
01:23:54,759 --> 01:23:56,211
The stars will change.

1110
01:23:57,185 --> 01:23:58,679
The earth and the sky will also change...

1111
01:23:58,720 --> 01:24:02,325
...but Hazari Prasad
won't forget this insult.

1112
01:24:03,367 --> 01:24:08,981
Hazari Prasad will remember it forever.

1113
01:24:09,684 --> 01:24:15,468
One day he will make you pay for this.
I'll surly make you pay for this.

1114
01:24:16,477 --> 01:24:17,675
Raja, let's go.

1115
01:24:25,724 --> 01:24:27,762
RAJA: <i>Excuse me, Madam.
I want to meet Mr. Mehra.</i>

1116
01:24:27,949 --> 01:24:29,382
FEMALE: <i>He is
very busy right now.</i>

1117
01:24:29,406 --> 01:24:31,393
RAJA: <i>It's very
important that I meet him.</i>

1118
01:24:31,642 --> 01:24:32,396
RAJA: <i>I must meet him.</i>

1119
01:24:32,436 --> 01:24:34,672
FEMALE: <i>Okay, wait here.
I will just check up.</i>

1120
01:24:35,060 --> 01:24:36,634
Write to Bennet and Miranda that...

1121
01:24:36,675 --> 01:24:39,593
...we liked their proposals and
ask them to send the details.

1122
01:24:39,955 --> 01:24:41,117
- Excuse me, sir.
- Yes.

1123
01:24:41,155 --> 01:24:43,515
Someone called Raja wants to meet you.

1124
01:24:46,115 --> 01:24:49,864
Tell him that I don't
have time to meet him.

1125
01:24:50,324 --> 01:24:52,192
Okay, sir. I am sorry.

1126
01:24:52,287 --> 01:24:53,286
So what was I saying?

1127
01:24:53,358 --> 01:24:54,537
You were saying something
about Bennet and Miranda.

1128
01:24:54,578 --> 01:24:55,930
I want to say something to you.

1129
01:24:56,137 --> 01:24:59,384
Write to them that we are not
at all interested in their proposal.

1130
01:24:59,555 --> 01:25:00,938
Sir, listen to me.

1131
01:25:00,979 --> 01:25:04,569
Write to them that talking
further about this is useless.

1132
01:25:04,888 --> 01:25:06,668
It would be just the waste of my time.

1133
01:25:06,721 --> 01:25:09,148
You have an issue with my father.
Why are you punishing me?

1134
01:25:09,189 --> 01:25:11,389
Write further that it was our mistake...

1135
01:25:11,430 --> 01:25:13,606
...to think they were
capable of this proposal.

1136
01:25:13,676 --> 01:25:17,343
Had I known earlier that
they were so unfit and cheats...

1137
01:25:17,368 --> 01:25:17,837
Should I also write that?

1138
01:25:17,877 --> 01:25:20,030
- Note it down, Varma.
- Yes, sir.

1139
01:25:20,691 --> 01:25:22,793
At least think about Madhu.

1140
01:25:22,925 --> 01:25:24,161
Why are you spoiling her life?

1141
01:25:24,274 --> 01:25:28,135
- Also write to them that we don't
need their cheap advice. - Right.

1142
01:25:29,835 --> 01:25:31,237
Then listen to me.

1143
01:25:31,673 --> 01:25:34,388
Like other marriages take
place without your permission...

1144
01:25:34,986 --> 01:25:37,554
...this marriage will take place
without your permission too.

1145
01:25:37,982 --> 01:25:41,039
So, finally you've shown your true colours.

1146
01:25:42,104 --> 01:25:46,443
If you drag this matter
further I will get you killed.

1147
01:25:47,278 --> 01:25:49,000
I am talking to you politely and you...

1148
01:25:49,041 --> 01:25:50,475
Will you teach me about propriety?

1149
01:25:51,240 --> 01:25:52,987
You have to be born with good manners.

1150
01:25:53,635 --> 01:25:57,372
You and your father have no manners at all.

1151
01:25:58,244 --> 01:26:01,395
Mr. Mehra, I used to respect you a lot.

1152
01:26:02,447 --> 01:26:06,788
But you are a very cheap person.

1153
01:26:07,289 --> 01:26:08,059
What did you say?

1154
01:26:22,875 --> 01:26:24,075
Call the police!

1155
01:26:24,613 --> 01:26:27,087
Get the security!

1156
01:26:34,723 --> 01:26:35,726
Stop this now!

1157
01:26:44,826 --> 01:26:46,139
Just stop it!

1158
01:26:56,875 --> 01:27:00,687
'There was a house here earlier,
but looks like ruins now.'

1159
01:27:00,867 --> 01:27:04,481
'Your face looks like the battlefield.'

1160
01:27:04,522 --> 01:27:06,251
Wonderful. Wonderful.

1161
01:27:06,582 --> 01:27:07,541
Have it, sir.

1162
01:27:07,808 --> 01:27:08,534
Hey!

1163
01:27:09,209 --> 01:27:11,456
What's going on?

1164
01:27:13,145 --> 01:27:16,926
'You are responsible for all this mess.'

1165
01:27:17,298 --> 01:27:20,091
'You are responsible for his torn pants.'

1166
01:27:20,453 --> 01:27:23,169
'Don't assume you will escape punishment.'

1167
01:27:23,210 --> 01:27:26,656
- 'I am Ghalib, the protector of the law!'
- Wonderful!

1168
01:27:26,704 --> 01:27:29,378
This is the guy. Inspector, arrest him.

1169
01:27:30,205 --> 01:27:31,493
Arrest him.

1170
01:27:31,557 --> 01:27:32,978
He creates a chaos.

1171
01:27:33,124 --> 01:27:35,857
I will put him in jail
and teach him a lesson.

1172
01:27:36,675 --> 01:27:39,700
- What? Father has put Raja in prison.
- Yes.

1173
01:27:42,289 --> 01:27:43,875
Isn't your father a lawyer?

1174
01:27:44,071 --> 01:27:45,479
Let's bail him out.

1175
01:27:45,570 --> 01:27:48,444
- My father can't bail him out today.
- Why?

1176
01:27:48,691 --> 01:27:51,425
Because today is Saturday.
The courts will open only on Monday.

1177
01:27:52,382 --> 01:27:53,500
Oh my God!

1178
01:27:54,320 --> 01:27:56,878
Raja will have to spend two days in prison.

1179
01:28:06,001 --> 01:28:06,852
Hey!

1180
01:28:09,001 --> 01:28:11,525
Are you trying to commit suicide?

1181
01:28:11,566 --> 01:28:13,583
- I will put you behind bars.
- Please do it.

1182
01:28:13,820 --> 01:28:16,027
No! I won't. I am in a good mood today.

1183
01:28:16,087 --> 01:28:18,161
- Yes. Come on!
- Listen!

1184
01:28:18,237 --> 01:28:19,619
Under which other crime
can you put me in prison?

1185
01:28:19,660 --> 01:28:21,847
- In what crime? Tell her.
- If you kill someone.

1186
01:28:21,888 --> 01:28:24,236
- If you pickpocket.
- If you rape someone.

1187
01:28:24,277 --> 01:28:27,384
- Also if you hit any officer.
- Oh! Thank you.

1188
01:28:30,035 --> 01:28:33,539
- You hit him really hard!
- Thank you.

1189
01:28:33,580 --> 01:28:37,986
- She has hit me. Now I will hit her.
- Yes, sure.

1190
01:28:39,327 --> 01:28:41,732
How dare you hit me?

1191
01:28:41,973 --> 01:28:43,534
You!

1192
01:28:45,315 --> 01:28:47,777
That was really hard. I won't spare you.

1193
01:28:47,822 --> 01:28:50,799
Help me! Help me!

1194
01:28:51,579 --> 01:28:55,056
[INDISTINCT]

1195
01:28:59,833 --> 01:29:00,997
Yes.

1196
01:29:01,187 --> 01:29:04,213
Civil police riots!
I will put you in prison for causing riots!

1197
01:29:04,238 --> 01:29:06,488
Section 920, come on!

1198
01:29:07,272 --> 01:29:11,276
After coming in here all
women stick to the right path.

1199
01:29:11,470 --> 01:29:12,496
You too will learn your lesson.

1200
01:29:14,743 --> 01:29:16,457
Come on! Get inside.

1201
01:29:25,515 --> 01:29:26,698
Raja!

1202
01:29:28,774 --> 01:29:30,193
Madhu, why are you here?

1203
01:29:30,732 --> 01:29:32,436
Do you remember both
of us had taken an oath?

1204
01:29:32,744 --> 01:29:34,430
Both of us will always be together.

1205
01:29:34,595 --> 01:29:41,145
That's why you were so
eager to come to prison.

1206
01:29:41,186 --> 01:29:42,972
The world has become so cruel...

1207
01:29:43,588 --> 01:29:47,983
...that prison is the only
place we can meet peacefully.

1208
01:29:48,234 --> 01:29:51,242
I had thought love had
vanished from the world.

1209
01:29:51,374 --> 01:29:55,322
But both of you have
made me forget my duty.

1210
01:29:55,913 --> 01:30:00,298
I am the protector of all
the lovers in this world.

1211
01:30:00,526 --> 01:30:03,977
Anybody who tries to destroy your love...

1212
01:30:04,213 --> 01:30:07,420
...will face my fury.

1213
01:30:08,074 --> 01:30:09,554
- Inspector!
- Yes.

1214
01:30:10,017 --> 01:30:12,321
Where is my son?
I am asking you, where's my son, inspector?

1215
01:30:12,362 --> 01:30:14,589
- His mother must know.
- My son's name is Raja.

1216
01:30:14,778 --> 01:30:17,889
For what crime have you put him in jail?
Set him free.

1217
01:30:18,004 --> 01:30:20,450
Is he your son?

1218
01:30:24,235 --> 01:30:26,958
- What is this girl doing in there?
- Laying eggs.

1219
01:30:26,999 --> 01:30:28,515
- What?
- She's laying eggs!

1220
01:30:28,809 --> 01:30:29,308
Madhu!

1221
01:30:35,169 --> 01:30:37,742
Who has dared to put
my daughter behind bars?

1222
01:30:37,864 --> 01:30:40,936
I did! I am the station master in-charge,
Mr. Ghalib!

1223
01:30:41,106 --> 01:30:43,623
I don't care who you are.

1224
01:30:43,664 --> 01:30:45,738
You will set my daughter free right now.

1225
01:30:45,779 --> 01:30:47,418
First my son should be set free.

1226
01:30:47,459 --> 01:30:48,480
First my daughter.

1227
01:30:48,505 --> 01:30:49,990
- My son!
- Quiet!

1228
01:30:50,715 --> 01:30:53,937
Neither your son will be
set free nor your daughter.

1229
01:30:53,977 --> 01:30:54,862
- Why?
- Why?

1230
01:30:55,379 --> 01:31:01,044
Because no one can be bailed
on a Saturday or a Sunday.

1231
01:31:01,228 --> 01:31:05,068
Neither a friend nor
a buddy can I set free.

1232
01:31:05,144 --> 01:31:07,064
- Wonderful!
- Quiet!

1233
01:31:07,916 --> 01:31:11,673
I don't care about the bail.
I'll call up the commissioner right now.

1234
01:31:12,786 --> 01:31:15,896
I can't compromise on my duty.

1235
01:31:16,038 --> 01:31:19,097
I can't set them free without bail.

1236
01:31:19,144 --> 01:31:19,786
[WHISTLE]

1237
01:31:19,826 --> 01:31:21,966
- Wow!
- Very good! Very good!

1238
01:31:21,995 --> 01:31:23,795
Such a shameless girl she is...

1239
01:31:23,830 --> 01:31:26,456
...she didn't leave my son in the jail too.
Shameless girl!

1240
01:31:26,593 --> 01:31:28,818
His son is shameless, tell him.

1241
01:31:28,997 --> 01:31:30,992
Useless, thug, vagabond, loafer.

1242
01:31:31,033 --> 01:31:33,987
- Hey, dare you call my son a loafer.
- Shut up!

1243
01:31:35,080 --> 01:31:39,104
This is not your house.
It is a police station.

1244
01:31:39,467 --> 01:31:41,831
I'll put you behind bars
if you talk too much.

1245
01:31:42,340 --> 01:31:44,513
Learn a lesson from your children.

1246
01:31:45,157 --> 01:31:48,816
Look! They are so much in love.

1247
01:31:53,019 --> 01:31:54,257
- Madhu!
- Raja!

1248
01:31:54,424 --> 01:31:56,150
- What is this?
- What is this?

1249
01:31:56,191 --> 01:31:58,064
- This is love.
- Inspector, stop them.

1250
