1499
01:57:26,291 --> 01:57:27,844
- I won't tell you.
- Won't you tell me?

1500
01:57:28,105 --> 01:57:30,070
Fine. Fine. I will tell you.

1501
01:57:30,185 --> 01:57:31,290
I will tell you.

1502
01:57:33,755 --> 01:57:34,896
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

1503
01:57:35,201 --> 01:57:36,176
Mother had come here yesterday.

1504
01:57:37,840 --> 01:57:38,937
Really?

1505
01:57:39,296 --> 01:57:40,532
She only gave me these bangles.

1506
01:57:41,766 --> 01:57:43,183
She told me that a married woman's wrist...

1507
01:57:43,341 --> 01:57:44,749
...should never be void of any bangles.

1508
01:57:50,331 --> 01:57:52,744
What happened, Raja?

1509
01:57:54,124 --> 01:57:57,019
Madhu, return these bangles.

1510
01:57:57,636 --> 01:57:59,817
Return them! Why?

1511
01:58:00,706 --> 01:58:02,115
These are mother's blessings.

1512
01:58:02,182 --> 01:58:03,636
No doubt these are mother's blessings.

1513
01:58:04,126 --> 01:58:05,384
But the gold belongs to my father.

1514
01:58:06,464 --> 01:58:07,929
I am not greedy for gold, Raja.

1515
01:58:08,526 --> 01:58:10,773
I just didn't want to
insult mother's feelings.

1516
01:58:11,119 --> 01:58:12,642
You are misunderstanding me, Madhu!

1517
01:58:13,265 --> 01:58:14,725
Even I don't want to
insult mother's feelings.

1518
01:58:14,781 --> 01:58:16,681
- But that's what you are doing.
- No, Madhu.

1519
01:58:17,128 --> 01:58:18,994
The man who has not
accepted you till now...

1520
01:58:19,451 --> 01:58:21,860
I can never accept the bangles
that have come from his house.

1521
01:58:23,427 --> 01:58:26,153
We just want their blessings.
Not their wealth.

1522
01:58:26,378 --> 01:58:28,075
You are just speaking rubbish, Raja.

1523
01:58:28,416 --> 01:58:29,951
I will not take off these bangles.

1524
01:58:30,071 --> 01:58:31,304
Then I will have to take them off!

1525
01:58:35,360 --> 01:58:36,256
Fine.

1526
01:58:36,612 --> 01:58:39,685
So then you go and return these bangles.
Go!

1527
01:58:59,795 --> 01:59:02,231
MADHU: <i>I have not
behaved properly with Raja.</i>

1528
01:59:03,383 --> 01:59:05,264
<i>Without any reason, I made him upset.</i>

1529
01:59:06,373 --> 01:59:09,214
<i>Poor guy.
He left without even eating anything.</i>

1530
01:59:10,866 --> 01:59:14,321
<i>When he comes back,
I'll ask him to forgive me.</i>

1531
01:59:14,896 --> 01:59:16,740
<i>I will feed him with my own hands.</i>

1532
01:59:20,174 --> 01:59:21,479
<i>It is evening now.</i>

1533
01:59:22,285 --> 01:59:23,865
<i>Why hasn't Raja come back yet?</i>

1534
01:59:24,920 --> 01:59:25,962
<i>Did anything happen...</i>

1535
01:59:26,639 --> 01:59:28,831
<i>No. This cannot happen.</i>

1536
01:59:29,873 --> 01:59:31,528
<i>He has gotten angry with me and went away.</i>

1537
01:59:31,718 --> 01:59:32,890
<i>Wherever he is right now...</i>

1538
01:59:33,024 --> 01:59:34,828
<i>...I will convince him and bring him back.</i>

1539
01:59:37,707 --> 01:59:40,867
Ramu hit his son a lot.
I was unable to tolerate it.

1540
01:59:41,045 --> 01:59:44,063
I explained it to him well.
But he did not understand.

1541
01:59:44,350 --> 01:59:45,941
- He went on hitting him.
- Uncle!

1542
01:59:46,309 --> 01:59:49,265
- Did Raja come here?
- No, daughter. He did not come here.

1543
01:59:50,664 --> 01:59:51,603
Then where did he go?

1544
01:59:52,645 --> 01:59:53,873
What happened, dear?

1545
02:01:38,121 --> 02:01:39,294
Where were you for such a long time?

1546
02:01:40,738 --> 02:01:41,538
Answer me!

1547
02:01:45,132 --> 02:01:46,666
- Madhu, I...
- Don't touch me!

1548
02:01:47,874 --> 02:01:49,332
What do you think of yourself?

1549
02:01:50,088 --> 02:01:52,975
Did you even think once, how tense I
would be? What would I go through?

1550
02:01:53,029 --> 02:01:55,295
- Madhu, listen to me at least.
- To hell with Madhu.

1551
02:01:56,139 --> 02:01:58,811
Because of a small mistake,
you left me and went away.

1552
02:01:59,295 --> 02:02:02,580
Is this your love for me?
Am I worth only this much?

1553
02:02:02,605 --> 02:02:05,365
- No, Madhu. It is not like that.
- I don't want to hear anything.

1554
02:02:07,089 --> 02:02:08,978
Did we leave home for this?

1555
02:02:10,519 --> 02:02:11,583
You don't know that...

1556
02:02:11,995 --> 02:02:14,784
...in these small moments
I have died many deaths.

1557
02:02:14,980 --> 02:02:16,579
I will never forgive you.

1558
02:02:16,862 --> 02:02:18,957
I hate you! I hate you!

1559
02:02:19,107 --> 02:02:21,424
I hate you! I hate you!

1560
02:02:23,103 --> 02:02:24,442
I hate you!

1561
02:02:26,515 --> 02:02:28,944
[SOBBING]

1562
02:02:45,829 --> 02:02:49,054
Didn't mother tell you that...

1563
02:02:50,283 --> 02:02:53,725
...a married woman's wrist should
never be void of any bangles?

1564
02:02:59,305 --> 02:03:03,260
I am sorry. Please forgive me.

1565
02:03:06,087 --> 02:03:07,174
I am sorry.

1566
02:03:09,675 --> 02:03:13,672
Promise me that you will never leave me.

1567
02:03:16,037 --> 02:03:17,786
I don't want anything else besides you.

1568
02:03:18,749 --> 02:03:19,714
Nothing else!

1569
02:03:21,029 --> 02:03:22,752
I love you, Raja!

1570
02:03:29,091 --> 02:03:30,053
Madhu!

1571
02:03:35,635 --> 02:03:36,812
I am really hungry.

1572
02:03:39,120 --> 02:03:40,339
I did not eat anything since morning.

1573
02:04:08,274 --> 02:04:09,502
Raja!

1574
02:04:10,517 --> 02:04:12,475
I have come to meet you.

1575
02:04:14,908 --> 02:04:17,725
I have come to meet you.

1576
02:04:20,653 --> 02:04:21,722
I...

1577
02:04:26,656 --> 02:04:28,614
Aunt. Oh Aunt!

1578
02:04:28,671 --> 02:04:30,284
What is the matter, Madhu?

1579
02:04:30,999 --> 02:04:34,378
My husband is working on the 12th floor.

1580
02:04:34,774 --> 02:04:36,831
I want to tell him something.

1581
02:04:36,962 --> 02:04:39,727
You please tell him.
He is unable to hear me.

1582
02:04:39,877 --> 02:04:41,250
What do you want to tell him?

1583
02:04:41,435 --> 02:04:45,468
Tell him that I love you.

1584
02:04:45,636 --> 02:04:46,901
Oh my God!

1585
02:04:49,963 --> 02:04:53,642
Silly girl,
have you come so far to say this?

1586
02:04:53,889 --> 02:04:57,038
Fine. All right. I will tell him that.

1587
02:04:57,153 --> 02:05:00,417
Ramu's father! Can you hear me?

1588
02:05:00,532 --> 02:05:02,670
What is the matter, Laajo?

1589
02:05:02,920 --> 02:05:05,129
I love you.

1590
02:05:05,224 --> 02:05:06,384
What?

1591
02:05:09,280 --> 02:05:12,352
I was eager to hear this
since the last 25 years.

1592
02:05:12,397 --> 02:05:14,279
Shall we take a holiday and go home?

1593
02:05:14,947 --> 02:05:16,829
I am not saying that.

1594
02:05:16,937 --> 02:05:22,198
The girl downstairs wants
to say this to her husband.

1595
02:05:22,267 --> 02:05:25,377
Oh my Laajo!
I've become excited after 25 years.

1596
02:05:25,421 --> 02:05:27,994
But you ruined all my intentions.

1597
02:05:28,479 --> 02:05:29,714
Never mind!

1598
02:05:29,755 --> 02:05:33,057
- Raja, my son!
- What is the matter, Uncle?

1599
02:05:33,098 --> 02:05:35,835
Your wife has sent a message for you.

1600
02:05:36,152 --> 02:05:37,956
She says I love you.

1601
02:05:44,118 --> 02:05:48,764
Uncle, tell her that I have
liked her style very much.

1602
02:05:49,255 --> 02:05:52,135
As a reward, I am coming down to kiss her.

1603
02:05:52,160 --> 02:05:53,536
All right.

1604
02:05:53,577 --> 02:05:55,479
- Oh my Laajo!
- What is the matter?

1605
02:05:55,587 --> 02:05:58,027
I am coming down to kiss you.

1606
02:05:58,460 --> 02:05:59,211
Oh my God!

1607
02:06:01,074 --> 02:06:03,301
You enjoyed it, right, Laajo?

1608
02:06:03,393 --> 02:06:06,033
Shut up! You are very shameless.

1609
02:06:07,502 --> 02:06:10,047
Is this the thing to be
said in front of everyone?

1610
02:06:10,356 --> 02:06:13,147
My dear wife, it's not me.

1611
02:06:13,424 --> 02:06:17,947
The lover upstairs will kiss his dear wife.

1612
02:06:18,093 --> 02:06:19,395
All right.

1613
02:06:20,434 --> 02:06:21,817
Hey, daughter!

1614
02:06:21,909 --> 02:06:27,450
What do you say...
He is coming downstairs to kiss you.

1615
02:06:29,875 --> 02:06:31,484
- Aunt.
- Yes.

1616
02:06:31,525 --> 02:06:34,635
Tell him not to come down. I am going home.

1617
02:06:34,689 --> 02:06:37,569
Madhu! Please don't go. I am coming.

1618
02:06:37,691 --> 02:06:40,571
Don't come down! I am leaving.

1619
02:06:40,680 --> 02:06:41,936
I am coming.

1620
02:06:49,780 --> 02:06:51,430
Raja!

1621
02:07:08,420 --> 02:07:11,324
Yes, Doctor. It's an emergency.
Please come immediately.

1622
02:07:11,799 --> 02:07:14,478
- Nurse, arrange for the blood.
- Yes, sir.

1623
02:07:14,519 --> 02:07:15,494
Please. Hurry up!

1624
02:07:15,519 --> 02:07:18,819
- Please save my Raja!
- We are trying our level best, Madam.

1625
02:07:19,282 --> 02:07:20,624
The patient's condition is very serious.

1626
02:07:20,786 --> 02:07:22,964
You arrange for at least Rs.1 lakh.

1627
02:07:23,555 --> 02:07:24,973
You don't worry about the money, Doctor.

1628
02:07:25,315 --> 02:07:27,799
I will bring as much money as possible.
You just arrange for the operation.

1629
02:07:27,855 --> 02:07:29,951
[THUNDERCLOUDS]

1630
02:07:49,039 --> 02:07:51,637
Madam, where are you going?
Sir and grandma have gone out.

1631
02:07:52,085 --> 02:07:52,994
Where have they gone?

1632
02:07:53,048 --> 02:07:54,995
They have gone out of town.
I don't know when they'll return.

1633
02:08:15,908 --> 02:08:18,906
You! For what have you come here? Go away!

1634
02:08:19,015 --> 02:08:21,452
Listen to me at least.
Raja has met with an accident.

1635
02:08:21,628 --> 02:08:23,514
What? Where is Raja?

1636
02:08:23,670 --> 02:08:25,473
He is breathing his
last in the hospital now.

1637
02:08:26,134 --> 02:08:29,279
We have to get him operated.
I need Rs.1 lakh for that.

1638
02:08:29,304 --> 02:08:31,231
If the operation is not
done as soon as possible...

1639
02:08:31,332 --> 02:08:32,637
...then he may not survive.

1640
02:08:32,751 --> 02:08:35,134
Please save my Raja! Please save my Raja!

1641
02:08:35,190 --> 02:08:36,685
Please take me to my Raja.

1642
02:08:37,049 --> 02:08:38,176
Fine. You both go to the hospital.

1643
02:08:38,307 --> 02:08:40,595
- I will bring the money and come there.
- Let's go!

1644
02:08:54,682 --> 02:08:56,515
[VOICE OVER] <i>Have you
gone mad, Hazari Prasad?</i>

1645
02:08:56,940 --> 02:08:58,486
<i>You are being sentimental about your son...</i>

1646
02:08:58,594 --> 02:09:00,724
<i>...and helping your enemy's daughter.</i>

1647
02:09:01,078 --> 02:09:02,686
<i>Have you forgotten the day when that scum,
Mehra...</i>

1648
02:09:02,727 --> 02:09:04,629
<i>...had slapped you
amongst a huge gathering?</i>

1649
02:09:05,045 --> 02:09:08,457
<i>Hazari Prasad, this is the right
moment to avenge your insult.</i>

1650
02:09:08,596 --> 02:09:09,936
<i>Do not let it slip off from your hands.</i>

1651
02:09:10,106 --> 02:09:11,994
<i>Do not let it slip off from your hands,
Hazari Prasad.</i>

1652
02:09:18,442 --> 02:09:20,970
Mother, why hasn't father come yet?

1653
02:09:21,554 --> 02:09:22,999
Don't worry, dear.

1654
02:09:23,232 --> 02:09:24,830
He must be on his way with the money.

1655
02:09:30,746 --> 02:09:31,204
Wait!

1656
02:09:31,245 --> 02:09:33,470
[THUNDERING CLOUDS]

1657
02:09:35,121 --> 02:09:36,711
You love Raja very much, isn't it?

1658
02:09:39,809 --> 02:09:42,469
- Then what can you do for Raja?
- Anything.

1659
02:09:42,785 --> 02:09:44,895
But let Raja get operated first.

1660
02:09:44,955 --> 02:09:46,646
Every second is very precious for him.

1661
02:09:48,282 --> 02:09:49,860
And Raja is precious for me.

1662
02:09:50,000 --> 02:09:51,195
Then what do you want?

1663
02:09:51,475 --> 02:09:52,719
Your Mangalsutra [Symbol of marriage].

1664
02:09:52,796 --> 02:09:55,507
[THUNDERING CLOUDS]

1665
02:09:57,095 --> 02:09:59,907
What are you saying? Have you gone mad?

1666
02:09:59,974 --> 02:10:01,953
Mad people do not speak in their senses.

1667
02:10:01,994 --> 02:10:04,055
Do not instigate a married
woman to curse you.

1668
02:10:04,349 --> 02:10:07,349
A married woman's curse changes destiny.

1669
02:10:07,586 --> 02:10:11,001
Then whatever happens,
even God cannot change it.

1670
02:10:11,055 --> 02:10:13,768
I don't know what form
her curse would take.

1671
02:10:13,883 --> 02:10:16,043
Stop this rubbish!
Or you'll have to face the consequences.

1672
02:10:16,100 --> 02:10:18,924
You are not a human being.
You are a demon. You are a beast!

1673
02:10:18,981 --> 02:10:20,297
Yes. I am a demon. I am a beast.

1674
02:10:20,523 --> 02:10:23,288
But who turned me into a beast?
This girl's father.

1675
02:10:23,403 --> 02:10:25,362
He has embarrassed me. He has insulted me.

1676
02:10:25,518 --> 02:10:27,160
He slapped me amongst a huge gathering.

1677
02:10:27,185 --> 02:10:29,202
But why are you making the
daughter pay for her father's mistake?

1678
02:10:29,396 --> 02:10:30,487
Give the bag to me!

1679
02:10:30,663 --> 02:10:32,921
[THUNDERING CLOUDS]

1680
02:10:32,962 --> 02:10:35,121
Do not dare to interfere in my affairs.

1681
02:10:35,267 --> 02:10:37,373
Get lost from here. Otherwise
our relationship will come to an end.

1682
02:10:37,414 --> 02:10:38,981
- Go away from here. Go!
- Listen to me.

1683
02:10:39,140 --> 02:10:41,004
Go away from here!

1684
02:10:42,174 --> 02:10:43,653
Now you listen to me carefully.

1685
02:10:43,765 --> 02:10:45,734
If your husband dies then
don't hold me responsible.

1686
02:10:46,269 --> 02:10:49,340
I plead to you.
For God's sake, please don't do this.

1687
02:10:49,381 --> 02:10:51,064
I am not doing all this for God.
I am doing all this for my sake.

1688
02:10:51,105 --> 02:10:54,596
But if Raja is my husband he is your son,
too.

1689
02:10:54,637 --> 02:10:57,455
My son died the day
he got married to you...

1690
02:10:57,586 --> 02:10:59,436
...and put this Mangalsutra
around your neck.

1691
02:10:59,637 --> 02:11:02,571
My success lies in this necklace.
Give it to me.

1692
02:11:03,471 --> 02:11:05,238
This is not just an ordinary necklace.

1693
02:11:06,321 --> 02:11:08,586
In each black bead of this
necklace all those nights...

1694
02:11:08,611 --> 02:11:10,287
...of Karva Chauth [Fasting day for
husband's long life] are entwined...

1695
02:11:10,531 --> 02:11:13,413
...when I had prayed for
the well being of my husband.

1696
02:11:13,820 --> 02:11:16,105
If you would have asked me for my
life I would have gladly given it to you.

1697
02:11:16,550 --> 02:11:18,587
But how can I give my Mangalsutra to you?

1698
02:11:19,125 --> 02:11:22,038
You are wasting your tears and my time,
you foolish girl!

1699
02:11:22,079 --> 02:11:24,135
- I am leaving.
- No!

1700
02:11:24,277 --> 02:11:28,103
Please don't do this.
Please do not separate me from Raja.

1701
02:11:28,144 --> 02:11:29,962
I cannot live without him.

1702
02:11:30,175 --> 02:11:32,212
I will die.

1703
02:11:32,359 --> 02:11:33,136
Then die!

1704
02:11:33,925 --> 02:11:34,985
Stop!

1705
02:11:35,972 --> 02:11:40,149
I am ready to do whatever you say.

1706
02:11:44,712 --> 02:11:47,405
Come on. Swear by your husband that...

1707
02:11:47,430 --> 02:11:50,002
...after today, there won't be any
relation between him and you. Come on.

1708
02:11:50,806 --> 02:11:52,176
From today onwards, you will not meet him.

1709
02:11:52,217 --> 02:11:53,877
You will never ever cross his path.

1710
02:11:53,918 --> 02:11:55,924
You'll never tell him why
you stopped meeting him.

1711
02:11:55,965 --> 02:11:57,763
I bind with the oath of the
relationship of a husband and wife.

1712
02:11:57,804 --> 02:11:59,658
From now on you and Raja
are not husband and wife.

1713
02:11:59,699 --> 02:12:02,159
If you break this promise,
you'll see Raja dead.

1714
02:12:02,199 --> 02:12:03,056
No.

1715
02:12:03,747 --> 02:12:07,050
I agree. I agree.

1716
02:12:08,109 --> 02:12:11,952
[THUNDERING CLOUDS]

1717
02:12:45,035 --> 02:12:52,353
"You should always be alive."

1718
02:12:52,653 --> 02:12:58,699
"I pray only for that."

1719
02:12:59,400 --> 02:13:06,802
"If death comes, let it take me."

1720
02:13:07,119 --> 02:13:12,830
"You should be spared all the pain."

1721
02:13:13,802 --> 02:13:20,903
"I have just done it once.
I have fallen in love with you."

1722
02:13:21,040 --> 02:13:28,787
"I have just done it once.
I have fallen in love with you."

1723
02:13:33,147 --> 02:13:33,943
Dear...

1724
02:13:34,723 --> 02:13:36,671
Doctor. How is my Raja?
Please tell me, Doctor.

1725
02:13:36,712 --> 02:13:37,984
There is no need to worry now.

1726
02:13:38,143 --> 02:13:40,436
He is out of danger.
If you want, you can see him.

1727
02:14:35,206 --> 02:14:36,323
[HORN HONKING]

1728
02:14:40,621 --> 02:14:43,012
Hey! He has dashed a girl!

1729
02:14:43,455 --> 02:14:45,164
Oh God!

1730
02:14:46,607 --> 02:14:48,184
Excuse me. Move.

1731
02:14:49,235 --> 02:14:53,095
Oh my God! Madhu! Daughter!

1732
02:14:54,819 --> 02:14:57,473
- Guard. Driver, bring some water.
- Sir, water.

1733
02:15:02,237 --> 02:15:03,461
My child!

1734
02:15:05,603 --> 02:15:06,453
Daddy!

1735
02:15:07,408 --> 02:15:09,486
- Daddy, I want to die.
- No.

1736
02:15:09,875 --> 02:15:10,876
I want to die.

1737
02:15:10,916 --> 02:15:13,147
No, child.
I'll not let you die, my daughter.

1738
02:15:13,740 --> 02:15:15,994
Who has done this to you? Who is he?

1739
02:15:16,097 --> 02:15:18,308
[CLUNKS]

1740
02:15:29,974 --> 02:15:32,345
Mr. Mehra! What is this that I am seeing?

1741
02:15:32,619 --> 02:15:35,567
A rich man's daughter, in this condition.

1742
02:15:35,947 --> 02:15:37,979
It seems she has not eaten for many days.

1743
02:15:38,020 --> 02:15:40,283
Whereas Mr. Mehra has four hotels.

1744
02:15:41,157 --> 02:15:42,017
Look at her clothes!

1745
02:15:42,115 --> 02:15:44,003
She doesn't even have
proper clothes to cover herself.

1746
02:15:44,044 --> 02:15:46,618
Mr. Mehra has six mills of cloth.

1747
02:15:47,113 --> 02:15:49,089
Ladies and gentlemen,
maybe you all don't know him...

1748
02:15:49,130 --> 02:15:51,280
...but I know Mr. Mehra very well.

1749
02:15:51,721 --> 02:15:55,110
Seeing all this,
I am unable to believe my eyes.

1750
02:15:55,540 --> 02:15:57,346
The daughter whose one sob would shake...

1751
02:15:57,387 --> 02:15:59,564
...the very foundation
of Mehra Industries...

1752
02:16:00,143 --> 02:16:01,687
...the same daughter
is like a corpse today.

1753
02:16:01,851 --> 02:16:02,739
Hazari!

1754
02:16:03,077 --> 02:16:05,041
There is no use of shouting, Mr. Mehra.

1755
02:16:05,677 --> 02:16:07,784
Just have some pity on
your daughter's condition!

1756
02:16:08,352 --> 02:16:13,992
So gentlemen, this helpless girl
fell in love and ran away from home.

1757
02:16:14,998 --> 02:16:18,909
As it always happens,
her lover threw her out of the house.

1758
02:16:19,622 --> 02:16:21,708
Now why did he throw her out?
I don't know anything about that.

1759
02:16:21,733 --> 02:16:23,233
Only Mr. Mehra can enlighten you on that.

1760
02:16:23,607 --> 02:16:26,208
But I have a request.

1761
02:16:26,785 --> 02:16:28,931
If there is some good marriage
proposal then let him know.

1762
02:16:29,303 --> 02:16:30,507
Do not worry about the money.

1763
02:16:30,763 --> 02:16:33,818
Mr. Mehra has lots of money!
You will get a big dowry.

1764
02:16:33,904 --> 02:16:36,241
We are not so shameless that we
will use the things which others...

1765
02:16:36,412 --> 02:16:37,767
...have used and thrown.

1766
02:16:39,132 --> 02:16:40,569
Did you hear him, Mr. Mehra?

1767
02:16:40,928 --> 02:16:43,170
Now your daughter
has just two options left.

1768
02:16:43,365 --> 02:16:46,360
Either she commits suicide
or she can become a prostitute.

1769
02:16:46,385 --> 02:16:49,194
- Shut your mouth, Hazari!
- You shut your mouth, Mehra!

1770
02:16:52,704 --> 02:16:56,113
Take my shawl and cover this corpse.

1771
02:16:56,844 --> 02:17:00,492
It is a bit worn out because
it belongs to a scrap vendor.

1772
02:17:00,892 --> 02:17:03,772
But it is sufficient to cover
your daughter's dignity.

1773
02:17:04,485 --> 02:17:09,250
Also take this bowl and start
begging for your daughter's life.

1774
02:17:10,164 --> 02:17:12,350
Remember one thing, Mehra.

1775
02:17:13,354 --> 02:17:18,116
The slap that cannot be seen hurts more.

1776
02:17:21,020 --> 02:17:22,288
Idiot!

1777
02:17:27,846 --> 02:17:29,770
You beast.

1778
02:17:32,722 --> 02:17:35,256
Take this, child. Have the medicine.

1779
02:17:36,187 --> 02:17:38,288
First tell me, where is Madhu?

1780
02:17:40,249 --> 02:17:42,045
Whenever I ask you,
you always evade the issue.

1781
02:17:43,529 --> 02:17:45,222
Why don't you tell me where is she?

1782
02:17:45,608 --> 02:17:47,517
How is she? She is fine, isn't it?

1783
02:17:47,877 --> 02:17:49,829
However she is, I want to see her.
I want to meet her.

1784
02:17:50,079 --> 02:17:52,646
- Where is Madhu, Mother?
- Do you want to know where Madhu is?

1785
02:17:53,166 --> 02:17:54,185
How she is?

1786
02:17:54,474 --> 02:17:55,478
Then listen to me, son.

1787
02:17:56,221 --> 02:17:59,535
The Madhu,
for whom you are in so much pain...

1788
02:17:59,627 --> 02:18:01,637
...has left you and gone
back to her father's house.

1789
02:18:02,044 --> 02:18:04,802
No! You are telling lies!
This is not possible.

1790
02:18:04,913 --> 02:18:08,439
Then why didn't she come to meet
you when you were fighting with death?

1791
02:18:08,665 --> 02:18:10,242
Because she was enjoying
herself at her father's house.

1792
02:18:10,479 --> 02:18:11,920
Thank God we reached there in time.

1793
02:18:11,961 --> 02:18:13,532
Otherwise there was
nobody to take care of you.

1794
02:18:13,573 --> 02:18:15,515
No! My Madhu cannot do this.

1795
02:18:16,203 --> 02:18:17,303
She cannot betray me.

1796
02:18:17,760 --> 02:18:20,590
Daddy, she can die for me,
but she cannot leave me alone to die.

1797
02:18:20,613 --> 02:18:22,852
You foolish boy!
The girl whom you are considering...

1798
02:18:22,942 --> 02:18:24,757
...to be your wife,
your beloved, your lover.

1799
02:18:24,798 --> 02:18:26,236
The girl whom you had married.

1800
02:18:26,336 --> 02:18:28,134
The girl around whose neck you
had put the holy Mangalsutra...

1801
02:18:28,245 --> 02:18:29,222
...she threw it on my face.

1802
02:18:29,312 --> 02:18:31,220
The Mangalsutra which you had given to her.
Look.

1803
02:18:35,514 --> 02:18:37,295
You are telling lies. You are telling lies.

1804
02:18:37,387 --> 02:18:40,563
If you trust your eyes more than my
word then go and see it for yourself.

1805
02:18:40,748 --> 02:18:43,587
See whether your Madhu even recognises you.
Go and see.

1806
02:18:44,590 --> 02:18:47,330
[SCREAMING] Madhu!

1807
02:18:52,131 --> 02:18:53,999
[DOOR CREAKING]

1808
02:18:54,040 --> 02:18:55,258
Madhu!

1809
02:19:11,290 --> 02:19:13,287
'Swear by the pure relationship
of a husband and wife.'

1810
02:19:13,347 --> 02:19:15,075
'From today onwards,
Raja and you are not husband and wife.'

1811
02:19:15,207 --> 02:19:18,394
'And if you break this promise
then you will see Raja dead.'

1812
02:19:19,722 --> 02:19:20,654
Hi, Madhu!

1813
02:19:22,657 --> 02:19:23,827
I have brought flowers for you.

1814
02:19:30,537 --> 02:19:33,571
- Come, Shakti!
- You are looking gorgeous.

1815
02:19:34,858 --> 02:19:37,614
You are so nice. You care so much for me.

1816
02:19:53,134 --> 02:19:54,629
- Come, Shakti.
- Yes, come on.

1817
02:19:57,210 --> 02:19:59,479
Raja, you!

1818
02:20:00,257 --> 02:20:01,329
Why?

1819
02:20:02,289 --> 02:20:03,855
Are you upset to see me alive?

1820
02:20:08,514 --> 02:20:13,075
Madhu, I never thought
that you would stoop so low.

1821
02:20:15,267 --> 02:20:16,646
When my father told me that...

1822
02:20:17,561 --> 02:20:20,844
...you left me alone in the
hospital in critical condition...

1823
02:20:21,928 --> 02:20:24,022
...I did not believe him.

1824
02:20:25,561 --> 02:20:29,668
But now I have realised
that my father was right...

1825
02:20:30,855 --> 02:20:32,744
...and my love was false.

1826
02:20:36,966 --> 02:20:38,346
Why are you quiet, Madhu?

1827
02:20:39,279 --> 02:20:40,272
Answer me.

1828
02:20:42,098 --> 02:20:43,361
Say something, Madhu.

1829
02:20:43,652 --> 02:20:44,971
What was lacking in my love?

1830
02:20:46,433 --> 02:20:48,222
Madhu, what wrong had I done that...

1831
02:20:48,396 --> 02:20:50,270
...you punished me so badly?

1832
02:20:51,389 --> 02:20:54,794
Look Raja, I have been used to a
luxurious life since my childhood.

1833
02:20:55,600 --> 02:20:58,732
By staying with you,
my requirements couldn't be fulfilled.

1834
02:21:01,018 --> 02:21:04,583
Moreover, after your accident,
neither did I want to live as a widow...

1835
02:21:04,990 --> 02:21:07,412
...nor did I want to
live as a cripple's wife.

1836
02:21:10,856 --> 02:21:13,667
No. No, Shakti.

1837
02:21:15,769 --> 02:21:17,026
Let him go.

1838
02:21:17,827 --> 02:21:19,528
This poor fellow is not
in his senses right now.

1839
02:21:19,569 --> 02:21:21,336
In fact, I have come to my senses now.

1840
02:21:22,845 --> 02:21:26,601
I have loved you, Madhu.
I will always love you.

1841
02:21:27,737 --> 02:21:31,624
But whatever you did to me,
please don't tell it to anybody.

1842
02:21:32,595 --> 02:21:34,417
Otherwise people will lose faith in love.

1843
